It would be great to have a wysiwyg guide, just as we have the notation guide. 

It could have a 'How do I?' section - it might include screenshots explaining the wysiwyg editor's UI.

How do I, for example, create a h3. header in a doc.?  -> I had to mouse over each menu item before finding the fomat section, which I experimented with to find the h3 header. It worked well but it was hard to find.

It would be helpful to be able insert wiki markup into the wysiwyg view without having to switch the view.

If, when in wysiwyg mode, I add 

{anchor:foo}{anchor}

to a page, it is saved as 

\{anchor:foo\}\{anchor\}

Would it be possible to provide some kind of ability in the editor to select pieces of text which should not be escaped? That way pre-wysiwyg users could work comfortably in the wysiwyg view, without having to switch views. This would help the learning process, as I could do whatever I wanted on the page but take my time when learning how to use the new editor. It would also mean that I do not have to issue another request to the server if I want to change views, which can be frustrating if the network is slow.

